  "response": "No, pre-board exam marks are not typically used to calculate the CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) for Class X. The CGPA is usually calculated based on the marks obtained in the final board examinations conducted by the respective education board (like CBSE, ICSE, or state boards).\n\nPre-board exams are internal practice exams conducted by schools to:\n1. Help students prepare for the final board exams\n2. Identify areas of improvement\n3. Predict potential performance in the board exams\n\nThe marks from pre-board exams are used for:\n- Giving students practice\n- Providing feedback to students and parents\n- Helping students understand their current level of preparation\n\nThe final CGPA is calculated using the marks from the actual board examination at the end of Class X.",
